During a press briefing, White House Deputy Press Secretary Karine Jean-Pierre addressed the recent shooting at an elementary school in Nashville, Tennessee. She expressed the President's appreciation for the first responders and offered prayers for the affected families. Jean-Pierre emphasized the need for action to address gun violence and called on Congress to pass measures such as the assault weapons ban, closing loopholes in the background check system, and requiring safe storage of guns. She also discussed the President's response to the deadly tornadoes in Mississippi, including the approval of a disaster declaration and federal funding for recovery efforts. Jean-Pierre announced that President Biden will be traveling to Durham, North Carolina, to kick off the Investing in America tour, highlighting the impact of the administration's economic agenda on communities across the country. She also discussed the administration's stance on taxes, student debt relief, and energy policy.